-- Tampa Bay Rays Promote Ex-Yankees Outfielder Matsui From Minors
-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 2012-05-29T19:11:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/tampa-bay-rays-promote-ex-yankees-outfielder-matsui-from-minors.html
The Tampa Bay Rays promoted former
 New York  Yankees outfielder Hideki Matsui from Triple-A Durham,
the team said on Twitter.  The Rays signed Matsui, 37, to a minor-league contract a
month ago. He played for the Yankees from 2003-09, then one
season each with the Los Angeles Angels and Oakland Athletics.
He has 173 home runs and batted .285 in the major leagues.  He was 2 for 11 in three games for Durham.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  